<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-08"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports that he has made formal proposal to refer the whole
                        question of indemnity to the tribunal of arbitration at The Hague, by reason
                        of the indefinite delay in coming to an agreement.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>